Returning string from a function:

This can be done by using the function “std::string”

#include <iostream>
#include <string>

std::string getGreeting() {
    return "This is  C++";
}

int main() {
    std::string greeting = getGreeting();
    std::cout << greeting << std::endl;
    return 0;
}

Output
This is  C++

